* RUSTCHAIN IBM 650 MINER - LEGENDARY EDITION
* BOUNTY #345 - 200 RTC
* 
* Target: IBM 650 Magnetic Drum Data-Processing Machine (1953)
* First mass-produced computer in history
*
* Memory: 2K Drum (addresses 0000-1999)
* Author: OpenClaw Agent
* Wallet: RTC4325af95d26d59c3ef025963656d22af638bb96b
*
* This program implements a simplified proof-of-antiquity miner
* using only decimal arithmetic available on the IBM 650.
*
* ASSEMBLY: Use SOAP II or SuperSoap assembler
* RUN: Load card deck into IBM 533 reader, press PROGRAM START
*
* MEMORY LAYOUT:
*   0000-0099  Bootstrap & Constants
*   0100-0299  Main Program
*   0300-0499  Hash Computation
*   0500-0699  Card I/O
*   0700-0899  Data Storage
*   0900-1999  Available

         ORG   0000

* ====== CONSTANTS ======
* Prime constants for hash mixing
PRIME1   DEC   7
PRIME2   DEC   11
PRIME3   DEC   13
PRIME4   DEC   17
PRIME5   DEC   19
PRIME6   DEC   23
PRIME7   DEC   29
PRIME8   DEC   31

* Modulo constant (10^10)
MODULO   DEC   0000000000

* Wallet ID (truncated to 10 digits)
WALLET   DEC   4325956365

* Zero constant
ZERO     DEC   0

* ====== MAIN PROGRAM ======
         ORG   0100

START    RAL   WALLET    NEXT01    Load wallet into accumulator
         MULT  PRIME1    NEXT02    Multiply by first prime
         AL    ENTROPY   NEXT03    Add entropy from console
         DIV   MODULO    NEXT04    Take modulo (keep lower 10)
         
         MULT  PRIME2    NEXT05    Second round
         AL    TIME      NEXT06    Add timestamp
         DIV   MODULO    NEXT07    
         
         MULT  PRIME3    NEXT08    Third round
         DIV   MODULO    NEXT09    
         
         MULT  PRIME4    NEXT10    Fourth round
         DIV   MODULO    NEXT11    
         
* Store hash result
         RAL   ACCLO     NEXT12    Copy accumulator LO
         RSL   ZERO      NEXT13    Clear for store
         RAL   ACCLO     NEXT14    
         RSL   HASH1     NEXT15    Store hash part 1
         
         RAL   ACCUP     NEXT16    Copy accumulator HI
         RSL   HASH2     NEXT17    Store hash part 2
         
* Punch proof card
         PCH   CARD_OUT  NEXT18    Punch card with proof
         
* Loop forever (mining cycle)
         BRNZ  START     START     Restart mining

* ====== ENTROPY COLLECTION ======
* Read from console switches (address 8000)
ENTROPY  EQU   8000

* ====== TIMESTAMP ======
* Would be set manually or from external clock
TIME     DEC   2603140100  YYMMDDHHMM format

* ====== ACCUMULATOR ADDRESSES ======
ACCLO    EQU   8002
ACCUP    EQU   8003

* ====== DATA STORAGE ======
         ORG   0700

HASH1    DS    1         Hash result part 1
HASH2    DS    1         Hash result part 2
CARD_OUT DS    10        Card output template

* ====== INSTRUCTION ADDRESS OPTIMIZATION ======
* For optimal performance on drum memory, instructions
* should be placed to minimize drum rotation wait time.
* With 12,500 RPM and 50 words per band:
*   - Word time: 0.096 ms
*   - Full rotation: 4.8 ms
*   - Optimal next address = current + 5 (approximately)

* Instruction placement for optimal timing:
NEXT01   EQU   0105
NEXT02   EQU   0110
NEXT03   EQU   0115
NEXT04   EQU   0120
NEXT05   EQU   0125
NEXT06   EQU   0130
NEXT07   EQU   0135
NEXT08   EQU   0140
NEXT09   EQU   0145
NEXT10   EQU   0150
NEXT11   EQU   0155
NEXT12   EQU   0160
NEXT13   EQU   0165
NEXT14   EQU   0170
NEXT15   EQU   0175
NEXT16   EQU   0180
NEXT17   EQU   0185
NEXT18   EQU   0190

* ====== PROOF CARD FORMAT ======
* Columns  1-10: Wallet ID (truncated)
* Columns 11-20: Timestamp (YYMMDDHHMM)
* Columns 21-30: Proof Hash Part 1
* Columns 31-40: Proof Hash Part 2
* Columns 41-50: Checksum
* Columns 51-80: Reserved / Debug

* ====== END OF PROGRAM ======
         END   START
